{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784002057176977627,"compiled_state":{"alias":"strange-checkered-nuthatch","assignee":"Joe Oakhart","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"HMAC-SHA256","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","head_sha":"1131b491bb26e5bc3932f1af26023ccac24567c5","key_id":"412fa5372ad877e0","kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 297d-a233-ce1b-4484","material: ed7dc77616bfc75e","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 8","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (1131b491b)","regver: 8952be2f5b88eba7","verified-at-sha:1131b491bb26e5bc3932f1af26023ccac24567c5"],"signature":"0595b25d33357440acdb2fd9c625bfa87e7f556fcd333c8f9db1df49aae7cbd8","signed_at":1783999556523838000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","authorship":{"signed":0,"unsigned":7},"authorship_ledger":[],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-207_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"8309b909-b742-470c-83a4-e3c51bc85e4a","comments":[],"created_at":1783967948791664001,"deps":[],"description":"## Why\n\nStand up authenticated-authorship SIGNING for every environment that writes ticket\nevents, so `identity.require_authenticated` CAN be enabled later. The actual flag flip\nis OUT OF SCOPE here (setup only). A write is signed iff a current identity resolves\n(via `.rebar/current_identity` or a `git config user.email` match to an identity ticket)\nAND `identity.signing_key`/`REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` points to that identity's OpenSSH\nPRIVATE key (`_commands/_seam.py:264-325`). Gate-exempt types: session_log, code_review,\nidentity.\n\n## What (delivered via child tasks)\n\n1. **Bootstrap the Rebar Bot identity** — none exists today (`rebar list --type identity`\n   is empty; only an HMAC key + Gerrit deploy key exist). Generate an ed25519 keypair,\n   create the identity ticket (email `joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com`), TOFU-register the\n   public key. Shared by AWS + GitHub.\n2. **Local dev** — per-developer identity + key + docs.\n3. **AWS review-bot + auto-lander** — SSM-stored signing key; the auto-lander comments on\n   work tickets (non-exempt) so it MUST sign; the review-bot writes only exempt types.\n4. **GHA reconcile-bridge** — CODE FIX: its inbound writer bypasses the signing seam and\n   stamps no author fields; route it through the seam (or stamp+sign) + inject the key.\n5. **GHA reconcile-bridge-canary** — inject key + flip committer email to the bot.\n6. **Test remediation** — defensive autouse conftest guard.\n7. **Confirm CI verify-identity mounts the tickets store.**\n\n## Scope\n\nSchema default `identity.require_authenticated` STAYS False (`_config_schema.py:316`).\nDo NOT set the flag true in `rebar.toml` in this story. The Gerrit HTTP password (code\npush) and the new SSH authorship key are SEPARATE credentials that coexist per env.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All child tasks closed.\n- [ ] A Rebar Bot identity ticket exists with a registered public key; its private key is stored securely per environment (SSM for AWS, Actions secret for GitHub), never committed.\n- [ ] Each ticket-event-writing environment (local, AWS auto-lander, GHA reconciler + canary) produces SIGNED events attributable to the correct identity when signing is exercised.\n- [ ] `require_authenticated` is NOT flipped in `rebar.toml`; schema default remains False.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88"]],"parent_id":"8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88","parent_status_uuid":"64b7e58b-b9e2-4302-a7ae-faad87af4efb","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"297d-a233-ce1b-4484","ticket_type":"story","title":"Stand up authenticated-identity signing for all ticket-event writers (setup only; flag flip out of scope)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["2b9f9108-af2b-4d2b-b3e7-95d5c9f8690b","228a0dec-abd4-485e-9397-3b0d35efc272","48fd1c18-31c0-47b4-bc0d-4cabd04b2848","6db43727-e3ed-46a7-93ac-32367ab805f7","64b7e58b-b9e2-4302-a7ae-faad87af4efb","71840cea-3491-4a0d-b518-95cfbac98853","6fc32917-13f0-4a47-9be6-3eccda6b9ba2"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784002057176977627,"uuid":"83251727-3e40-46c5-81d9-e0879e01b92c"}